Of course! Decorators in Python can be implemented in a class method by using the `@` symbol to attach the decorator function to the class method. Here's an example:
```
class MyObject:
    def my_method(self):
        # Some code here
        return "This is my method"

    @my_decorator
    def my_method(self):
        # Some additional code here
        return "This is my method with decorator"
```
